name: Vincent A. CIANCI, Jr. et al. v. The PROVIDENCE CITY COUNCIL et al.

parties: Vincent A. CIANCI, Jr. et al. v. The PROVIDENCE CITY COUNCIL et al.

opinions.text:
ORDER
Since the petition for writ of certiorari is not accompanied by adequate supporting material, said petition for certiorari and petitioners’ motion for stay are both denied.

attorneys: Vincent J. Piccirilli, Providence, for petitioners.
Ronald H. Glantz, City Sol., Providence, William Y. Chaika, Cranston, for respondents.
casebody.head_matter:
Vincent A. CIANCI, Jr. et al. v. The PROVIDENCE CITY COUNCIL et al.
No. 80-578-M.P.
Supreme Court of Rhode Island.
Jan. 5, 1981.
Vincent J. Piccirilli, Providence, for petitioners.
Ronald H. Glantz, City Sol., Providence, William Y. Chaika, Cranston, for respondents.
